{"doc": "the women who broke free from ohio 's ' house of horrors ' after a decade in captivity have revealed for the first time in their own words how they survived the traumatic ordeal\ncastro and castro recalled the years of rapes , torture and psychological games at the hands of castro , a man who lived close to their homes in ohio , and managed to lure them into his house with trust because his daughters were the girls ' friends\nthe brave survivors have written a book , hope : a memoir of survival in ohio , which will be released on april 27\nin an excerpt , published in people magazine this week , castro and gina , revealed how they found the strength to survive imprisonment\nthe survivor has described in her new memoir , how her daughter gave her the strength to go on during the harrowing ten - year ordeal castro , 29 , revealed in her first - person memoir about her abduction and imprisonment by castro , that she was left confused by conflicted feelings towards him when he was kind to their daughter , whom she gave birth in captivity after being raped castro , 25 , also shared the details of her horrifying ordeal in a new memoir with castro , being published later this week castro recalled how she had learned from tv news that her mother died of a heart attack , aged 43 , in march 2006 , while she was ' chained like a dog ' in castro 's home\nat this point , the teen had been missing for three years\ncastro lured her into his home on april 21 , 2003 , on a promise to see his daughter , her acquaintance\nhe barricaded the 16 - year - old in a room , told her to pull down her pants and raped her\nshe was then chained in the basement and repeatedly abused\nfour days after she was captured , castro turned on the news and saw her mother pleading for her safe return\nshe said that a silent castro watched louwana miller beg for her daughter to come home\n' he has an odd look on his face , and then i realize : he 's proud , ' castro wrote about her monstrous captor\nshe also described in the people interview how castro was much stronger than he looked , packing muscle beneath his rotund figure\n' to be around him was scary , ' castro recalled\n' he had these cold black eyes\nwe were afraid we were going to die\n' the ohio ' house of horrors ' survivors have written a book , being published on april 27 castro was abducted using a similar ploy by castro a year later\nshe described her abductor to people as ' always prepared '\nit later emerged that castro , now 34 , had been imprisoned in a separate bedroom since august 2002\na month after learning that her mother , louwana miller , had died , castro , realized she was pregnant by castro in april 2006\nalthough initially elated , she worried how castro would react\ncastro wrote : ' i think my mom sent me this baby\nit 's her way of giving me an angel\nbut i worry about what he 's going to do\n' castro told me that he beat her to make her miscarry\nwill he let me carry my baby ? ' as the pregnant teen mourned her mother alone amid harrowing torture and abuse , she recalled how she made video tapes of news reports of her mom at vigils and watched them repeatedly\ncastro wrote in the memoir : ' i would rewind and hear her voice\ni feel like she 's definitely here with me now\n' on christmas day , she gave birth in her prison of a home to daughter , jocelyn , with the help of castro\ncastro appeared delighted to have a new daughter , castro wrote\nshe recalled : ' when the baby started kicking , i reached for his hand and placed it on my stomach\n' i knew the baby would be safer if he was excited about being a new father\n' castro told her that they were ' a family '\nthe predator took the little girl , whom he called pretty , to church and out to play while her mother remained in chains in his filthy , dilapidated home\ncastro finally took the chains off the three women when jocelyn started to notice them , even though castro tried to protect her daughter by telling her that they 